    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix error propagation in MPDCCH DMRS initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe `init_mpdcch_dmrs_tab` function in the LTE transport module was declared as `void` and didn't return any error status, causing failures to be silently ignored downstream. When invalid OFDM symbol size values were passed to the function, it would proceed with incorrect calculations without reporting the error, potentially leading to undefined behavior in MPDCCH processing.\n\nThe root cause was missing input validation and error propagation in the initialization function. This fix changes the function to return an error code, adds parameter validation, and updates the calling function to check for errors.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/edci.c`: \n  - Changed `init_mpdcch_dmrs_tab` return type from `void` to `int`\n  - Added validation for OFDM symbol size parameter (must be >= 128)\n  - Added proper error return codes (-1 for error, 0 for success)\n  - Updated `init_mpdcch` function to check for and handle initialization errors\n"
}